                                <date>1958</date>. С. <biblScope unit="page">??–??</biblScope>.</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><encodingDesc><tagsDecl>&amp;renditions;</tagsDecl></encodingDesc></teiHeader><text><body><entry xml:id="entry_bazyr" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>bazyr</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>bazur</orth></form><sense><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>крыло</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>wing</q></tr></sense><exampleGrp><example><quote>Xsærtæg fexsta æmæ (marǧæn) appærsta jæ bazyr</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>Хсартаг выстрелил и оторвал (у птицы) крыло</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Xsærtæg shot and tore off (bird's) wing</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>14</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>næmun æj rajdædtoncæ sæ bazurtæj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>они стали его бить своими крыльями</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>they began to hit him with their wings</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>31%l14%l—32%l1%l</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>arvæj zænxi astæw bazurginæj ka xætuj...</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>кто носится, крылатые, между небом и землей...</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>who rushes, feathered, between sky and ground</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>32%l12%l</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>(ostitæ) wærcci fæste nibbazurtæ ʽncæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>(женщины) устремились за перепелкой</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>(women) headed for a quail</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 118</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><exampleGrp><example><quote>Xsærtæg fexsta æmæ (marǧæn) appærsta jæ bazyr</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>Хсартаг выстрелил и оторвал (у птицы) крыло</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>Xsærtæg shot and tore off (bird's) wing</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_ОЭп."/><biblScope>14</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>næmun æj rajdædtoncæ sæ bazurtæj</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>они стали его бить своими крыльями</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>they began to hit him with their wings</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>31%l14%l—32%l1%l</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>arvæj zænxi astæw bazurginæj ka xætuj...</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>кто носится, крылатые, между небом и землей...</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>who rushes, feathered, between sky and ground</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_MSt."/><biblScope>32%l12%l</biblScope></bibl></example><example xml:lang="os-x-digor"><usg><lang/></usg><quote>(ostitæ) wærcci fæste nibbazurtæ ʽncæ</quote><tr xml:lang="ru"><q>(женщины) устремились за перепелкой</q></tr><tr xml:lang="en"><q>(women) headed for a quail</q></tr><bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#src_СОПам."/><biblScope>II 118</biblScope></bibl></example></exampleGrp><etym xml:lang="ru">Слова %ibazyr%i ‘крыло’ и <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bazyg"/> ‘рука’ заключают одну и ту же основу, но с разными формантами: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bazyg"/> восходит к %ibāzu%i-%ika%i, а %ibazyr%i к %ibāzu%i-%ira%i. Варианты с -%ika%i мы рассматриваем под <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bazyg"/>. Оформление -%irа%i мы также находим в ряде иранских языков: <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>bāzura</w> <gloss><q>рука</q></gloss></mentioned> в <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>snāvarə-bāzura-</w> <gloss><q>имеющий жилистые руки</q></gloss></mentioned> (= <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>nawær-bazur</w></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"><lang/> <w>b’zwr</w> <gloss><q>крыло</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/> <w>bāzul</w> <gloss><q>рука</q></gloss></mentioned> (?), <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/> <w>wazr</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ps"><w>wazar</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/> <w>wåzərgá</w> <gloss><q>крыло</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="oru"><lang/> <w>bázar</w> <gloss><q>рука</q></gloss></mentioned> и др. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"/><biblScope>95</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 111</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>18</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">The words %ibazyr%i ‘wing’ and <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bazyg"/> ‘arm’ contain the same stem but with different formants: <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bazyg"/> traces back to %ibāzu%i-%ika%i, and %ibazyr%i traces back to %ibāzu%i-%ira%i. Variants derived with -%ika%i are considered under the word <ref type="xr" target="#entry_bazyg"/>. The derivates with the formant -%irа%i are also found in a number of Iranian languages: <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>bāzura</w> <gloss><q>arm</q></gloss></mentioned> в <mentioned xml:lang="ae"><lang/> <w>snāvarə-bāzura-</w> <gloss><q>having arms with prominent veins</q></gloss></mentioned> (= <mentioned xml:lang=""><lang/> <w>nawær-bazur</w></mentioned>), <mentioned xml:lang="xpr"><lang/> <w>b’zwr</w> <gloss><q>wing</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="x-balochi"><lang/> <w>bāzul</w> <gloss><q>arm</q></gloss></mentioned> (?), <mentioned xml:lang="ps"><lang/> <w>wazr</w></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ps"><w>wazar</w></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="mnj"><lang/> <w>wåzərgá</w> <gloss><q>wing</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="oru"><lang/> <w>bázar</w> <gloss><q>hand</q></gloss></mentioned> etc. (<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Morgenstierne._EVP"/><biblScope>95</biblScope></bibl>).%n<bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._ОЭ"/><biblScope>II 111</biblScope></bibl>. — <bibl><ref type="bibl" target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>18</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry></body></text></TEI>